    "A learned linear network converted the concatenation of matrices from all the attention heads back to a single contextualized output matrix of the original dimension.",
    "Intuition: Splitting the computational cost across attention heads leads to a tradeoff between token dimension and the number of attention heads.",
    "Larger dimension token vectors hold more information and improve model performance whereas multiple heads bring more diversity to the model.",
    "LLM developers are still experimenting to determine the best tradeoff between vector embedding dimension and the number of attention heads.",
    "The computation cost to generate co-relevance scores is quadratic in sequence length."
